The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 What We are Watching

Theatre - Dark Humour

A rehearsal in progress

 Measure for Measure

 The undergraduate and postgraduate students of Jadavpur University?s department of English stage the Shakespeare play under the direction of Prof Ananda Lal. Theatrecian presents the black comedy, written in 1604, which explores issues of power abuse and sexual morality using familiar Shakespearean conventions like disguise and mistaken identity.

 Catch it at Gyan Manch on December 9 at 6.30 pm

 Dolly Basu 

 Mrs Soriano

 The Choopkatha production presents Dolly Basu as and in Mrs Soriano, an adaptation of Eduardo de Filippo?s Filumena Marturano. Having served her master for 25 years, former prostitute Filumena tricks him into marrying her for a secure future when the old man plans to wed a young girl.

 The role has been made memorable in West End by Dame Judi Dench.

 Catch it at Girish Mancha on December 4 at 6.30 pm




